Class GlossaryService

java.lang.Object
  org.cast.cwm.glossary.GlossaryService

public class GlossaryService
extends Object

A service class for storing Glossary words in a data store. Configure this class to use your own implementation with #setInstance(GlossaryService).

newEntry

public IWritableGlossaryEntry newEntry()
Create and return a new IGlossaryEntry of the entryClass registered with this service class. By default this is a BaseEntry object, but applications can use their own class (which must implement IGlossaryEntry) by calling GlossaryService.setEntryClass(class) This method will only succeed if entryClass implements IWriteableGlossaryEntry; if you have unwritable glossary entries you need to construct them some other way.

Returns:
a new, blank object implementing IGlossaryEntry

newEntryModel

public org.apache.wicket.model.IModel<? extends IWritableGlossaryEntry> newEntryModel()
Return a new IGlossaryEntry wrapped in an appropriate sort of Model. Applications that define an IGlossaryEntry class that is linked to a datastore will want to override this to use a detachable model, for instance. This method will only succeed if entryClass implements IWriteableGlossaryEntry; if you have unwritable glossary entries you need to construct them some other way.

Returns:
properly model-wrapped blank glossary entry.
